Hi @Trovats!

The ` $("#tabs").tabs({  activate: ... });` code is specifically for jQuery UI tabs, so that block of code isn't needed.

To make tablesorter work within Bootstrap tabs, you need to bind to the shown event ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/njj5b5vc/4/)):

```js
$('a[data-toggle="tab"]').on('shown.bs.tab', function (e) {
    // find the active tab, and update the widgets
    $('.tab-pane.active').find('table').trigger('applyWidgets');
});
```

Additionally, if you redefine the theme values:

```js
$.tablesorter.themes.bootstrap = {
    ...
}
```

either redefine them all, or use jQuery extend to preserve the values that aren't set..

```js
$.extend($.tablesorter.themes.bootstrap, {
    table: 'bootstrap',
    caption: 'caption'
});
```

