@plang85 thank you very much for your contribution Philipp. It would be very nice to support JSON for general compatibility and inter-operation of systems.

I would like to comment on the naming standard that I want to preserve through this project. I tried to name functions and properties with respect to their usages. For instance, you can use `knotvector_u` when you want to access the knot vector on the u-direction in the Surface object. This is very similar in reading control points. I believe that renaming `read_json` to something like `read_ctrlpts_json` would maintain easy readability in the documentation and easy access to the functions when using syntax completion in IDEs.

I also think that it would be better to move `parse_json` to `utilities.py` in order to reuse it for the Surface class. In that case, it will probably need some modification, but I think it should be easy to add a flag to function signature to choose between Surface and Curve classes.

