I have found two options so far, but I am not an expert on sphinx or CSS, so perhaps I am missing something.

1.)  reintroduce a local copy of sphinx gallery and then modify the local `gallery.css` as before.
 
2.)  A second workaround seems to be appending the following CSS code to the bottom of the existing [custom.css](https://github.com/scikit-image/scikit-image/blob/master/doc/source/themes/scikit-image/static/css/custom.css) file.  I had to add `!important` flags here CSS or these settings did not end up overriding the settings in sphinx-gallery's own `gallery.css`.  These settings all appear to be within a `sphx-glr` CSS namespace, so I don't think it causes any effects outside the gallery.  
```css

/*
Overrride some default settings in sphinx-gallery's gallery.css */
.sphx-glr-thumbcontainer {
  border: solid #d6d6d6 1px !important;
}

div.sphx-glr-download {
  width: auto !important;
}

div.sphx-glr-footer {
    text-align: left  !important;
}

div.sphx-glr-download a {
  background-color: #d9edf7 !important;
  border: 1px solid #bce8f1 !important;
  background-image: none !important;
}

div.sphx-glr-download code {
  color: #3a87ad !important;
}

div.sphx-glr-download a:hover {
  background-color: #d9edf7 !important;
}

p.sphx-glr-signature a.reference.external {
  display: none !important;
}
```

A drawback of the second approach is that it could break or need tweaking depending on the version of sphinx-gallery used to build the docs.  For example, I had to introduce the line below about `background-image: none` to get the blue background to show up in the buttons rather than an image gradient of yellows as used in current sphinx-gallery.

