@jirikuncar The idea is not to solve the issue. It is to make migrations as easy as possible. There will always be conflicts (example: user accounts id which have an integer as ID), but using UUIDs will make conflicts less frequent and simplify migrations: one of the community would change its name but the records would not need any modification. The record history would still make sense as it would be possible to know in what community records where before without guessing previous community names.

PIDStore are needed for records as there are many types of persistent identifiers for publications (DOI, ePIC PIDs, etc...). Whereas for communities I am not sure that we will need something else than one UUID and a name.
However is one use case which could justify it, if the communities also have ORCID IDs or some other kind of IDs. If you think that this is a requirement for invenio-communities then it makes sense. B2Share does not have this requirement for now.

