An example of how you can work out the "create only" issue would be to add a `create_only_fields` attribute to your Endpoint and use that from the adapter. 
ie:

```python
class MyViewSet(viewsets.ModelViewSet):

    def get_serializer_class(self):
        if getattr(self, action, None) in ('list', 'retrieve'):
            return MyReadSerializer
        if getattr(self, action, None) == 'update':
            return MyUpdateSerializer
        return super(MyViewSet, self).get_serializer_class()
        
    
class MyEndpoint(Endpoint):
    (base_)serializer = MyCreateSerializer
    base_viewset = MyViewSet


class MyAdapter(BaseAdapter):
    metadata_info = [
        ...
        MetaDataInfo('create_only_fields', PROPERTY, []),
    ]
```

The in your for generation code, if the record is not a new one, you can check that the field is not listed in  `create_only_fields` before rendering it.

