@Yangqing that is almost true but TF only supports NHWC on CPU so we ended up inserting transpositions everywhere (and yes we were trying to leverage NCHW to NHWC conversion utilities in this case) and got quite a few complaints from users who look closely at what we generate. This arguable is a performance hit b/c you will only encounter such a problem on a CPU which has orders of magnitude lower throughput than a GPU and every transpose counts (ps. with a graph rewriter you cannot eliminate the first one, or maybe you can with annotated dimensions).

P.S. @dzhulgakov  TF does have something like that but operates on a lower level, i.e., https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/a0d784bdd31b27e013a7eac58a86ba62e86db299/tensorflow/compiler/xla/service/gpu/convolution_folding.h .
